      "text": "The trigger isn't a need. It's an old reflex flicking on with nothing behind it.\n\nYou may have noticed it already: certain everyday moments still whisper \"cigarette\" even though the desire itself is fading. The coffee. The end of a meal. Picking up the phone. Getting in the car. These are triggers — and understanding how they work removes their last bit of power.\n\nCBT focus today: Stimulus control & cue extinction — understanding conditioned cues and letting them fade through non-reinforcement."
